Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
First, when crossing the street, you must figure out where you want to go and what is the fastest way to get there.  Next, you have to find the nearest crosswalk and go to it.  Then, look to your left to see if any cars are coming. After that, look to your right to see if any vehicles are coming from that direction. Finally, you walk across the street calmly and carefully while looking back and forth in both directions.